        "file_path": "/workspace/django/middleware/cache.py",
        "old_string": "class UpdateCacheMiddleware(MiddlewareMixin):\n    \"\"\"\n    Response-phase cache middleware that updates the cache if the response is\n    cacheable.\n\n    Must be used as part of the two-part update/fetch cache middleware.\n    UpdateCacheMiddleware must be the first piece of middleware in MIDDLEWARE\n    so that it'll get called last during the response phase.\n    \"\"\"",
        "new_string": "class UpdateCacheMiddleware(MiddlewareMixin):\n    \"\"\"Response-phase middleware that caches pages to reduce database hits.\n\n    This middleware updates the cache after a view has been executed. It should\n    be placed as the FIRST middleware in the MIDDLEWARE list so it runs LAST\n    during the response phase (middleware executes in reverse order during\n    response phase).\n\n    Used together with FetchFromCacheMiddleware to implement a complete\n    full-page caching system. When used alone, use CacheMiddleware instead.\n\n    Configuration is controlled by these Django settings:\n    - CACHE_MIDDLEWARE_SECONDS (int): Default timeout in seconds for cached\n      pages (default: 600). Can be overridden by Cache-Control max-age header.\n    - CACHE_MIDDLEWARE_KEY_PREFIX (str): Prefix for cache keys (default: \"\").\n    - CACHE_MIDDLEWARE_ALIAS (str): Name of the cache backend to use\n      (default: \"default\").\n\n    Caching behavior:\n    - Only GET and HEAD requests are cached\n    - Only responses with status code 200 (or 304) are cached\n    - Responses with Cache-Control: private, no-cache, or no-store are skipped\n    - Responses that set cookies for cookie-less requests are skipped\n    - Cache duration is determined by (in order of priority):\n      1. page_timeout parameter (if set explicitly)\n      2. Cache-Control max-age header from response\n      3. CACHE_MIDDLEWARE_SECONDS setting\n\n    The middleware automatically sets/updates response headers:\n    - Cache-Control: with max-age value\n    - Expires: calculated expiration date/time\n    - Vary: request headers used for cache key generation (preserved)\n    - Age: for cached responses, the age of the cached content\n\n    Example:\n        MIDDLEWARE = [\n            'django.middleware.cache.UpdateCacheMiddleware',\n            # ... other middleware ...\n            'django.middleware.cache.FetchFromCacheMiddleware',\n        ]\n\n        # Or use a specific cache backend:\n        CACHE_MIDDLEWARE_ALIAS = 'my_cache'\n        CACHE_MIDDLEWARE_SECONDS = 3600  # 1 hour\n    \"\"\"",
        "replace_all": false
      },
